It’s giving I buy all my groceries at Erewhon level rich, it’s giving I go to Pilates at 1 p.m. level rich. It’s giving I vacation from November to the new year lever rich. Ok, you get the idea. But what we’re referring to is the new sneaker color trend we’re all over Los Angeles right now. Surprise surprise, it’s Pantone’s 2025 color of the year—mocha mousse. Even the name of the shade sounds luxurious.

We’ve seen L.A. locals incorporating the popular color throughout their outfits here and here. And when it comes to the shoe department, celebrities are already proving this sneaker trend that gives rich behavior is coming in hot and heavy as seen here.

As for today’s focus, we’re highlighting how everyone with rich taste in Los Angeles is styling mocha mousse sneakers.

Mocha mousse paired with brown and black make for an elevated and chic winter outfit. We love this combination for an afternoon of errands of to simply grab coffee.
